{"documents": ["I heard your screen name is a theorem", "[image: 212FD80BD46EA24F8D79A8DADE0E6B61.png]", "[emoji41]", "You already knew that", "[image: 211D3D8390634D4F00C1D2466AE495FF.jpg]", "[emoji13]", "Hahaha, Jonas's way of thinking is really something else", "By the way, do you have any movie or book recommendations? I heard from Tang Pang that you've seen some good movies (and suggested she write a review after watching [emoji212])", "[emoji13] For movies, just watch what you like—what others strongly recommend might not appeal to you.", "But since you asked, I'll recommend a few.", "[emoji13]", "In middle and high school I liked inspirational stuff, now I watch a bit of everything (●◡●)ﾉ", "Deep in the Heart (thriller, low-budget Chinese film, great narrative)\r\nThe Prestige (thriller, by Nolan who did Inception, great narrative and script)\r\nTriangle (thriller, brilliant script, mind-bending)\r\nThe Butterfly Effect (sci-fi, brilliant concept)\r\n12 Angry Men (black & white, unique narrative style)", "[emoji13] Yeah, I really like thrillers.", "Watch them when you have time [emoji13] If you like any, let me know and give me some feedback so I can recommend better [emoji13]", "Sure thing", "Are you studying physics now?", "Automation [emoji13]", "Haha, that reminds me of what Manzi said", "[emoji13]", "I'd really like to do grad school at Zhejiang University or Fudan, but I feel like the English requirements might be pretty high?", "What's your major again? /shiver", "Pharmacy [emoji182]", "[emoji13] Not sure, but good English does matter [emoji13] If you want to do grad school, aim for Peking University first!", "Are your classes taught in English?", "Some of the major courses are", "[emoji13] Though some of the older teachers' English isn't great either", "[emoji41]", "Is your academic pressure heavy? [emoji13]", "A bit. I just made it into the top ten, worried my rank might drop. The competition for grad school recommendation spots is pretty fierce.", "Hmm [emoji13] Stay positive—worst case you just take the exam.", "Yeah, things are good now. Our class has a nice vibe, a few good friends formed a study group and we often meet up to study.", "Get some sleep early.", "Okay, good night [emoji75]", "Jonas, are you guys okay? [image: B8E38D8542A2FCEEB1F168CE075FCA68.png]", "[emoji182] Thanks for caring", "I was lucky, didn't get infected", "Haha, so many people got infected [pout]", "[image: 2662A233B9FE48FADEC334BFB6ADBF8B.jpg]", "Glad you're okay [emoji193]", "[image: 1B3461F890A382DAF4381B4122B740A8.jpg]", "From what you posted, are you thinking of going straight to a PhD? [emoji182]", "Still trying to decide [emoji264]", "Oh I see", "Why a PhD in biology instead of pharmacology?", "Pharmacology and biology are pretty similar—both do cell work and mice experiments 👀", "Oh~", "I got offers for direct PhD: Fudan basic medicine (HBV research), Sun Yat-sen Cancer Center (oncology). Still deciding.", "Wow, congrats!", "A PhD is really tough [emoji182]", "(But I'm planning to go straight to PhD", "Haha yeah, PhD is four years now and there are fewer spots if you apply later. If you're set on a PhD, going straight is better [emoji21]", "True, a PhD does help with job hunting [emoji182]", "Yeah, and if the PhD is in a direction and with an advisor you like, that's even better.", "hhh so hard", "Where are you going, Jonas?", "Staying at my school, haven't had the interview yet [emoji182]", "Okay, good luck!", "[emoji124] 🙏"], "metadatas": [{"source": "chat_history", "sender": "Martha", "timestamp": "2019-04-05 23:52:34", "role": "target"}, {"source": "chat_history", "sender": "Martha", "timestamp": "2019-04-05 23:52:37", "role": "target"}, {"source": "chat_history", "sender": "Jonas", "timestamp": "2019-04-05 23:52:53", "role": "other"}, {"source": "chat_history", "sender": "Jonas", "timestamp": "2019-04-05 23:52:59", "role": "other"}, {"source": "chat_history", "sender": "Jonas", "timestamp": "2019-04-05 23:53:29", "role":